ISPF panels can be constructed to assist with applications for purposes such as data entry, running queries, and other common tasks.

Panels are defined using PDL (panel definition language) and are stored in panel libraries for use with REXX (or CLISTS).

Panel definitions are stored as members in a PDS called ISPPLIB.

The panel definition is divided into sections where attributes of fields are declared, then a processing section.

The procedure is:

1) use ISPF edit to create and edit a new member in ISPPLIB

2) test the appearance of the panel in ISPF 7

3) add REXX code to complete the app.
